In his 1986 book Engines of Creation: The Coming Era of Nanotechnology [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/a57971c8-ae9c-4ebe-a063-2706f31c4163?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], the scientist E=
ric Drexler envisioned a future where matter could be controlled and progra=
mmed at the atomic scale. For the most part, this vision hasn=E2=80=99t hap=
pened=E2=80=94with the exception being biology. While the =E2=80=9Cuniversa=
