erstanding of biology.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #4=
04040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The d=
ouble helix is considered to be the starting point for the field of </span>=
<strong>structural biology</strong><span>. The speed at which massive probl=
ems in genetics were solved based on the double helix caused a ripple effec=
t throughout the life sciences. It became possible to work at the </span><s=
